-- Research in Motion Agrees to Allow India to Monitor Blackberry, Times Says
-- Vipin Nair
-- 2010-08-03T01:43:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/research-in-motion-agrees-to-allow-india-to-monitor-blackberry-times-says.html

          
          
             Research in Motion Ltd. agreed for
the first time to allow Indian security agencies to monitor its
Blackberry services in a bid to avoid a government ban, the
Economic Times reported, citing telecommunications department
documents.  
 The company offered to share technical codes for corporate
e-mail services and open access to all consumer e-mails within
15 days, the daily said. Research in Motion will provide further
details on its proposals to Indiaâ€™s communications ministry
today, the report said.  
